  "why": "The paper explicitly constrains transformations to preserve image semantics and naturalness: (1) it searches the space of parametric, semantically-preserving metamorphic transformations (not arbitrary pixel-space mutations), (2) it manually tunes valid parameter domains (high/low boundaries) to keep transformations within semantics-preserving intervals, (3) it enforces an SSIM threshold and rejects mutated inputs whose SSIM to the original is too low, and (4) it adopts a conservative compound transformation policy (pixel-value changes followed by at most one affine transform) to avoid producing meaningless images. These controls are applied to the transformation search process (each candidate is a transformation within the tuned domain), preventing generation of unrealistic or semantically-invalid inputs across the fuzzing iterations. The authors also manually validated sampled outputs to mitigate tuning threats.",
